originalText: up_ewald
Start Element
ewald
If you try anything, you *will* bleed, zoner!

::You approach this person in an attempt to start a conversation. He responds with a glance, followed by him turning his head away from you. His face seems to be stuck in a perpetual frown, making him look like he is constantly angry. Whether he is or not, you remain unsure.::
::He faces you, but remains silent.::
context.loc_tch_entry_hostileWithTchortists
Excuse me, I had some questions I'd like to ask you.
::Leave him be.::

::He looks at you, waits a couple of seconds, then decides to respond.::

I'm not interested in answering any questions. Go bug someone else, zoner.

::He looks at you, waits a couple of seconds, then decides to respond.::

I don't care about your name, zoner. As far as those questions of yours are concerned... go bug someone else.
What can you tell me about yourself?
Why are you here and what can you tell me about this place?
What do you know about Tchortists?
So long.
context.npc_up_ewald_met

::He seems irritated by your question.::

Will you leave me alone already? Which part of the "go bug someone else!" line did you misunderstand?

::His frown becomes even more pronounced.::

Deaf, stupid or both?

::He spits his words through his teeth.::

Oh, what kind of a moron are you? Leave me alone or I'll zone you out on the spot!
Go - as in, get as far away from me as possible; bug - as in, annoy, rile, bother; someone else - as in, someone that is not me.
I'd say both. Therefore, I'll have to *lower* myself to your intellectual level so that I may be able to convey the message that I have been trying to convey for some time now. Here it is...
Get it now?
Duh... Duh duh... Duh... Shoo! Don't speak to me... ever again... duh duh... duh!
